status_message: I am asking everyone for a small favor. Just share the link if you can! In early September my dad was diagnosed with a brain tumor behind his right ear on the brain called Acoustic Neuroma. He had gone undiagnosed and had probably had it for 10-20 years without knowing it. It had grown large enough that it was causing him to have major migrane headaches as well as periodic vision flashes that would last up to 20 seconds. Fortunately it was a benign tumor that would not turn cancerous and could not spread. He had major brain surgery at Palmetto Health Baptist last Wednesday. The surgery took a total of 10 hours. He has been In the hospital since, and was in the ICU until Monday. With him never having any surgery before, he did not react well to all of the anesthesia and sedatives and it took him 5 days to come out of the deep sleep and loopy that he was experiencing. It was not a pretty site to see. I have set up a gofundme page to try to reach out to the community to help them out with their medical expenses. All I am asking is that you share this page/link in everyway you can. He is having to go to speech therapy and see therapists because the surgery left some palsy/paralysis on the side of the face that they operated on. https://www.gofundme.com/s48kmyvw P.S. - He is at home now and getting stronger each and every day! He is doing much better and getting back to his old self! It will take 3-4 months for a full recovery but he should get back soon without any complications, Praise God! Also, He is having to go to speech therapy and see therapists because the surgery left some palsy/paralysis on the side of the face that they operated on.
link_name: Click here to support Dad's Brain Surgery Recovery Fund by Graham McGee

status_message: PSA about Checker Yellow Cabs (the free USC cabs) Hey guys! I know this isn't related to rideshare but i'm trying to get the word out to as many USC student as possible. I just wanted to share what happened to my roommate last night when she took a yellow checked cab home. She was in five points and accidentally left her phone in the cab on the way back home. The man driving (when we called the company they said his name was Charles Adams but honestly this may not be his name) came back to our apartment complex and demanded that my roommate get in the car by herself and drive with him to an ATM. He told her that she had to pay him $125 or she wouldn't get her phone back. When the ATM wouldn't let her take out exactly $125 he made her give him $140. He wouldn't let her see the phone until he had the money so she wasn't even certain that he had it but since she was alone with him at that point she didn't want to argue. The cab number was 103 so I would recommend you all avoid that cab if possible. We contacted the cab company but they basically told us they weren't going to do anything about it. PLEASE be cautious taking the free cabs home. I'm sure many of the drivers are kind people but there are also people like this who are only concerned with getting as much money as possible. If any of you have any idea how we can get her money back or at least get this man fired please contact me. My roommate is incredibly upset and I'm not sure what steps we can take to fix this. Thank you!

status_message: We are leasing a 2 Bedroom/2.5 Bath 2 story townhome in Woodlands of Columbia, SC from May 2015-July 2015. We are looking for Subleasers for those months but you also could sign a new year lease for the home if you let the office of Woodlands know! Each room is $655 a month including utilities. It comes completely furnished in the living room and bedrooms. You can sublease one of the bedrooms if you are trying to find a room for yourself. There is a gym, nice pool, shuttle service to and from campus if you're taking summer classes, and great amenities at the club house. If you have any questions or you are interested please message me. We loved living here, it is a great location and very chill environment to live in.

status_message: Hey guys, not rideshare related but you may have seen other post about this but  I am a buyer for a company called bell tower books and basically what we do is buy back any text books and give you cash right there on the spot. It doesn't matter if it's in a binder, if it's old, torn, or new. And then as soon as you give me the book I would scan the bar code and it would tell me how much your book is worth and I would give you the cash and then keep your book. It's a lot easier then the bookstore and the amounts are usually higher then what the bookstore is willing to give you! You can message me on Facebook, email me at abby.herschman@gmail.com or text me at 4438601276  to set up an appointment and a time we can meet up and I can meet you anywhere on campus! And I'm a student too so I understand the stress of finals week and this is one less thing you have to worry about! And I will be available from now until early on Saturday the 13th to buy books! Thanks! Good luck with finals

group_name: University of South Carolina (USC) Rideshare group!
status_message: This group is for the University of South Carolina students who don't mind sharing the ride in exchange for gas money. Please don't forget to invite your friends. With more members there will no doubt be more rides to give. Want to travel anywhere around South Carolina? Maybe Charleston, Greenville, or somewhere in Georgia without spending a fortune on gas or flights, and with some good company? Put up a post if you're driving somewhere another student might want or need to go or if you need a ride and are willing to pitch in for gas! Put the dates you want to leave and return, where specifically you're going/want to go, etc. This group is a great way to find ways to travel cheaper, faster, and to get to know some cool people along the way! Invite everyone you know who goes to USC because the more people that join this group the more likely everyone will be able to find rides and passengers! Bon voyage! Ride Share is a carpool program in many major cities and colleges. If you need a ride post about it on the wall, and the idea is that another University of South Carolina student with planes on going to that same location will carpool with you for little or no cost. (GAS MONEY!!!)

group_name: University of Connecticut UConn Ridehsare Group!
status_message: Want to travel anywhere around Connecticut? Maybe to Boston, New Haven, Bridgeport or somewhere around New York, without spending a fortune on gas or flights, and with some good company? Put up a post if you're driving somewhere another student might want or need to go or if you need a ride and are willing to pitch in for gas! Put the dates you want to leave and return, where specifically you're going/want to go, etc. This group is a great way to find ways to travel cheaper, faster, and to get to know some cool people along the way! Invite everyone you know who goes to UConn because the more people that join this group the more likely everyone will be able to find rides and passengers! Bon voyage! Ride Share is a carpool program in many major cities and colleges. If you need a ride post about it on the wall, and the idea is that another University of Connecticut student with planes on going to that same location will carpool with you for little or no cost. (GAS MONEY!!!)
